# Expo: AI agents and LLMs

## Cursor: official Expo Skills (remote rule)

In **Cursor**: **Settings → Rules & Commands → Project Rules → Add rule → Remote rule**, add:

`https://github.com/expo/skills.git`

Remote skills are discovered when you work on Expo-related tasks (they are not slash commands).

## Bundled skill in this repo

See **`.cursor/skills/expo-mobile/SKILL.md`** for monorepo-specific commands, **Tailwind CSS / NativeWind** (plus remote skill `expo-tailwind-setup`), layout (`src/app`), and EAS.

## Expo Skills (official plugin)

| Skill | Use when |
|-------|----------|
| `building-native-ui` | Expo Router UI, styling, navigation, animations, native tabs |
| `expo-api-routes` | API routes in Expo Router + EAS Hosting |
| `expo-cicd-workflows` | `.eas/workflows/`, EAS build pipelines, CI/CD |
| `expo-deployment` | App Store, Play Store, web hosting, API routes |
| `expo-dev-client` | Dev clients, TestFlight |
| `expo-module` | Expo Modules API (Swift, Kotlin, TS), config plugins |
| `expo-tailwind-setup` | Tailwind v4 + react-native-css + NativeWind v5 |
| `expo-ui-jetpack-compose` | `@expo/ui/jetpack-compose` |
| `expo-ui-swift-ui` | `@expo/ui/swift-ui` |
| `native-data-fetching` | fetch, React Query, SWR, loaders, offline |
| `upgrading-expo` | SDK upgrades and dependency fixes |
| `use-dom` | Expo DOM / web code in webview |

## Documentation for LLMs (lower token cost)

- **Index**: `https://docs.expo.dev/llms.txt` (site-wide list of bundles)
- **Full**: `https://docs.expo.dev/llms-full.txt`
- **EAS**: `https://docs.expo.dev/llms-eas.txt`
- **SDK (latest)**: `https://docs.expo.dev/llms-sdk.txt`
- **Per-page markdown**: append **`/index.md`** to a doc page URL (e.g. `https://docs.expo.dev/develop/development-builds/create-a-build/index.md`)

For a **specific SDK** line, use versioned bundles when needed (e.g. `llms-sdk-v54.0.0.txt`).

## This app

- **SDK**: see `apps/mobile/package.json` (`expo` version).
- Prefer **`bun`** from repo root per monorepo conventions (`bun --cwd apps/mobile run …`).
